=Description=

"Denizen is a fast growing community that includes a diverse array of individuals: entrepreneurs, scholars, artists, activists, influencers, recording artists, designers, investors, nonprofit leaders, and more.   Amongst us are systems change leaders at the helm of organizations such as the Center for Humane Technology, Zebra’s Unite, Purpose, Mobius, Esalen, the Consilience Project, the Post Growth Institute, the Economic Security Project, One Project, and the Buckminster Fuller Institute.  Denizen was founded by former Googler, Stanford d.school Fellow, and Harvard Kennedy School graduate Jenny Stefanotti, who serves as our primary steward and curator. 

We are brought together by a shared desire to address the root causes of humanity’s current ecological and economic crises."
